In a 24 hour period, you are allowed to bring back $200 per person without paying Canadian duty. You are not supposed to bring back fruits and vegetables for pest control reasons.

Apparently food is considered a basic need so just like we aren't taxed on certain foods here in Canada we dont have to pay them when we cross. That being said its just from experience we haven't had an issue but its always a bit of a risk Im sure. So far no issues
